import azureml.core
from azureml.core import Workspace


subscription_id = "7c9d382c-5964-48db-9cf6-c595c7ba4339"
resource_group = "synapse-rg"
workspace_name = "synapse-aml"

ws = Workspace(subscription_id = subscription_id, resource_group = resource_group, workspace_name = workspace_name)

from pyspark.sql.functions import lit

df_orig = spark.sql("SELECT * FROM default.dailyrevenue")
df_orig = df_orig.withColumn('Forecasted', lit(0))
df_orig.show(10)

model_path = 'azureml://experiments/synapse-syn-dailyrevenue-20210408012050/runs/26f87a5b-83eb-494f-a976-7d726dbdfd18/artifacts/synapse-syn-dailyrevenue-20210408012050_artifact/'
model = mlflow.sklearn.load_model(model_path)

d = {
    'Date': pd.date_range(start='1/01/2018', end='2/01/2018')
}
pdf = pd.DataFrame(data=d)

pdf_forecast = model.forecast(pdf)[1]
pdf_forecast.reset_index(inplace=True)
pdf_forecast = pdf_forecast.rename(columns = {'index':'Date'})

print(pdf_forecast.head(5))

from pyspark.sql.functions import lit


df_forecast = spark.createDataFrame(pdf_forecast)
df_forecast = (df_forecast
    .select('Date', '_automl_target_col')
    .withColumnRenamed('_automl_target_col', 'Revenue')
    .withColumn('Forecasted', lit(20000))
)

df_forecast.show(5)

df = df_orig.union(df_forecast)

display(df) # create line graph to visualize the forecast
